		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The transistor doesn't matter at all, it's a common collector amplifier (voltage buffer, current amplifier). 2N3906 are fine.
<br />
<br /><img src="http://img832.imageshack.us/img832/2151/51048821.jpg" alt="Image" />
<br />
<br />I got those values off a modded Famicom but 200R and 120R would be better since they make exactly 75 ohm Zout.

		

