	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The PPU output is high impedance and unable to drive any TV directly, the transistor is just a simple buffer to beef up the signal. The weak signal from PPU will pick up noise form address lines etc. particularly notable if you just press you finger against the video out and some digital I/O line... the signal is very weak.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
